      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Model setup and execution followed a documented simulation protocol reviewed by two independent analysts (FDA and DePuy Synthes teams). Boundary condition application, material assignment, and contact pair definitions were independently verified by a third analyst. Pre-run checklist completed for all 33 simulation runs (3 solvers × 11 specimens). Post-processing scripts version-controlled and independently validated against manual extraction for 3 representative cases.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/use-error-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Documented simulation protocol with independent review required. Pre-run checklist completion mandatory for all runs. Post-processing independently validated for a representative subset. Achieved Gradation 2 meets required Gradation 2."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The FEA model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity formulation for Ti-6Al-4V (tangent modulus 1.2 GPa derived from tensile coupon data). Large-deformation kinematics (updated Lagrangian) activated for all analyses. Penalty-based frictionless contact at rod-screw interface (friction coefficient sensitivity study showed < 1.5% effect on stiffness, < 2.8% on yield force for μ = 0.0–0.3). UHMWPE block modeled as linear elastic (E = 0.96 GPa, ν = 0.46) consistent with literature. Model form uncertainty estimated at 2.1% of stiffness QoI based on comparison of three independent solver implementations.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/model-form-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Plasticity formulation must be validated against tensile coupon data. Large-deformation kinematics required for displacements exceeding 5% of characteristic length. Contact formulation sensitivity must be documented. Model form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the uncertainty budget. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Material properties (E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa, UTS = 950 MPa) derived from lot-specific tensile coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V ELI bar stock used to manufacture the test specimens (n=5 coupons per lot, two lots). Geometry inputs derived from coordinate measuring machine (CMM) measurements of three representative screws per lot (dimensional tolerance ±0.005 mm). Rod geometry from engineering drawings with CMM verification. Boundary conditions (applied displacement, fixture stiffness) measured during experimental setup and input directly to the model.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/model-inputs-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Material properties must be derived from lot-specific characterization of the same material batch used in testing. Geometry inputs must be verified by CMM or equivalent dimensional metrology. Boundary conditions must be measured, not assumed. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested: 6 at Laboratory 1 (FDA CDRH), 5 at Laboratory 2 (DePuy Synthes). All specimens drawn from the same production lot and characterized by CMM prior to testing. Specimen-specific geometry incorporated into individual FEA models enabling specimen-level comparison. Inter-specimen coefficient of variation for stiffness: 3.1% (Lab 1), 3.8% (Lab 2), consistent with manufacturing tolerance. Sample size justification: power analysis (α=0.05, β=0.20) confirmed N=11 sufficient to detect 10% mean difference.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/test-samples-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Minimum N=10 specimens required from a single production lot with CMM characterization. Specimen-specific geometry must be incorporated into individual FEA models. Sample size must be justified by power analysis. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (5 mm/min quasi-static compression-bending, 44 mm inter-screw span, ambient temperature). A second loading rate (1 mm/min) was considered but not executed due to resource constraints. The single test condition is a documented limitation; however, the quasi-static rate insensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V at the strain rates involved (< 0.001 s⁻¹) is well-established in the literature, and the ASTM F1717 standard specifies this condition as the reference for regulatory submissions. This shortfall is addressed by the offset rationale in the decision record.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/test-conditions-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Ideally, testing at two or more loading rates and at least one environmental condition (e.g., 37°C saline) to bracket the intended use space. Single ASTM F1717 standard condition achieved; shortfall justified by material rate insensitivity and regulatory standard specification. Achieved Gradation 2 is below required Gradation 3; offset rationale documented."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/equivalency-input-parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Traceability established between experimental inputs and FEA model inputs for all primary parameters: (1) material properties — same lot, coupon-tested; (2) geometry — CMM-measured per specimen; (3) boundary conditions — fixture stiffness measured at test setup (mean 18,400 N/mm, CV 1.2%); (4) applied displacement — crosshead displacement corrected for machine compliance using calibration data. Input equivalency matrix documented and reviewed by all three laboratory teams.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/equivalency-input-parameters-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Full input equivalency matrix required mapping all primary model inputs to experimental measurements. Fixture stiffness must be measured and incorporated. Machine compliance correction required. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) using both relative error (< 10% threshold) and E/uval metric (< 1.96 threshold per ASME V&V 10.1). All three QoIs passed both acceptance criteria across all N=11 specimens and both laboratories. Specimen-level scatter plots and Bland-Altman analysis documented. No systematic bias detected (mean signed error: stiffness +0.4%, yield force +0.7%, force at 40 mm +0.3%). Confidence interval overlap analysis confirms statistical equivalence at 95% level.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/output-comparison-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All primary QoIs must satisfy: relative error < 10% for all specimens; E/uval < 1.96 for pooled comparison. Bland-Altman analysis required to detect systematic bias. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/relevance-qoi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly linked to the regulatory submission decision. Construct stiffness is the primary predictor of clinical load sharing; yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation under worst-case intraoperative loading; force at 40 mm is the ASTM F1717 standardized comparative metric. Linkage between QoIs and clinical failure modes documented in the risk analysis (pedicle screw fracture, rod breakage, loss of fixation).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/relevance-qoi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoI acceptance criteria",
        "description": "QoIs must be traceable to ASTM F1717 standard outputs and to clinical failure modes identified in the device risk analysis. Linkage must be documented. Achieved Gradation 3 meets required Gradation 3."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cf/relevance-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
