      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the intended use scenario: ASTM F1717 static compression-bending of the exact non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design submitted for regulatory clearance, using the same material lot, same fixture geometry, and same loading protocol. Multi-laboratory execution (FDA CDRH + DePuy Synthes) provides independence and reduces risk of systematic laboratory-specific bias. The validation domain (geometry, material, loading) fully encompasses the COU operating envelope defined above.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
